  "prompt": "Someone deleted me on snapchat, so I deleted him & now he appears in my Added me section, but I cannot see his score. Does this mean he added me back?",
  "response": "When someone interacts with your Snapchat account\u2014such as adding or removing you\u2014they trigger specific notifications and status changes within the app. Based on your description, here's what's likely happening and what it means:\n\n### **Understanding the \"Added Me\" Section**\n\n- **\"Added Me\" Notification:** This section appears when someone sends you a friend request on Snapchat. If you see this person listed under \"Added Me,\" it typically means they've recently tried to add you back after being removed.\n\n### **Regarding the Snapscore Visibility**\n\n- **Snapscore Basics:** Your Snapscore is a combination of the total number of snaps you've sent and received, along with other activities on Snapchat.\n  \n- **Why You Might Not See His Snapscore:**\n  1. **Pending Acceptance:** If you've deleted someone and they subsequently try to add you back, they might appear in your \"Added Me\" list until you accept their friend request. During this pending state, certain details like their Snapscore might not be visible.\n  2. **Privacy Settings:** Snapchat allows users to control who can see their Snapscore. If the person has adjusted their privacy settings to hide their Snapscore from certain users or entirely, you won't be able to see it regardless of your friend status.\n  3. **Recent Re-addition:** If they\u2019ve just re-added you, there might be a short delay before all their profile information, including the Snapscore, becomes visible to you.\n\n### **Does This Mean He Added You Back?**\n\nYes, seeing him in the \"Added Me\" section generally indicates that he has sent you a friend request, which often means he's attempting to add you back on Snapchat. However, since you deleted him and then he tried to re-add you, you have the option to accept or decline his request:\n\n- **If You Accept:** Once you confirm the friend request, you'll both be reconnected on Snapchat, and his Snapscore (if visible) should appear in your friends list.\n  \n- **If You Decline or Don\u2019t Respond:** He might continue to appear in the \"Added Me\" section until you take action on his friend request.\n\n### **Next Steps**\n\n1. **Check Privacy Settings:** Ensure that neither of you has restrictive settings that might prevent the Snapscore from being visible.\n   \n2. **Accept the Friend Request:** If you're comfortable reconnecting, accept his request. This action should fully restore your friend status and display his Snapscore, assuming no privacy restrictions are in place.\n\n3. **Reach Out Directly:** If you're uncertain about the status or want clarification, consider sending a Snap or message (if possible) to communicate directly.\n\n4. **Wait for Updates:** Sometimes, Snapchat might take a short period to update friend statuses and associated information. Give it some time to see if the Snapscore becomes visible after appearing in \"Added Me.\"\n\n### **Additional Considerations**\n\n- **App Glitches:** Occasionally, Snapchat may experience glitches or delays in updating friend lists and Snapscores. If the issue persists beyond a reasonable timeframe, consider restarting the app or checking for updates.\n  \n- **Account Restrictions:** Ensure that neither account has any restrictions or blocks that might interfere with normal functionality.\n\nIn summary, seeing him in the \"Added Me\" section suggests that he's likely trying to add you back on Snapchat. The absence of his Snapscore could be due to pending acceptance, privacy settings, or temporary app delays. Reviewing your friend request and his privacy settings should help clarify the situation.",
